FBIS4-41813 "drsov124_f_94021" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 National Affairs Joint Venture Recycling Obsolete Munitions Joint Venture Recycling Obsolete Munitions LD2806105894 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2200 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2806105894 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] The recycling of Ukrainian ammunition which has exceeded its expiry date is now being conducted by the joint-stock company "Alliyant-Kiev," formed in 1993 by the Shostkinskiy scientific and research institute, the U.S. Alliyant-Tecsystems, and Repirbase Ltd of Great Britain. The Ukrainian partner has 51 per cent of the shares in the joint-stock company. In the first quarter, "Allyant- Kiev" already received 5,600 tonnes of ammunition for recycling. The 127 tonnes of extracted gunpowder were sent to the UkrVybukhBud explosives manufacturer and the 250 tonnes of brass cartidges to a nonferrous reprocessing factory to be reprocessed into rolled metal. According to unofficial sources at the Defense Ministry, there are 320,000 tonnes of ammunition stocks in line to be scrapped.
